<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870804-0058 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief::Kaufman andamp; Broad Inc.</HL><DD> 08/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> KB IRETENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Kaufman andamp; Broad Inc. said it signed a definitive agreement to acquire Capitol Life Insurance Co. of New York, a unit of Integrated Resources Inc.'s Capitol Life Insurance Co. subsidiary. Terms weren't disclosed. Kaufman andamp; Broad's Sun Life U.S.A. unit, a life insurance and financial services concern, operates in all states but New York. Capitol Life Insurance of New York had $24 million in assets at the end of 1986 and had more than $13 million in statutory capital and surplus, Kaufman andamp; Broad said. It said the acquisition is subject to regulatory approval but completion is expected by the end of 1987. Los Angeles-based Kaufman andamp; Broad, a home builder with interests in financial services and life insurance, had signed an agreement in 1984 to acquire all of Capitol Life Insurance Co. from a previous owner but didn't exercise its option to purchase the company. </TEXT></DOC>